  "body": "## ðŸŽ‰ Description\r\n\r\nThe idea of delayed tokens delivery. \r\n\r\n- [ ] ðŸ› This is a bug report.\r\n- [x] ðŸ“ˆ This is a feature request.\r\n\r\n## ðŸ“ Details\r\n\r\nNot all tokens should be available for transfers immediately after the distribution (minting). For example, we will be able to deliver tokens in 180 days after minting.\r\n\r\n## ðŸ”¢ Code To Reproduce Issue\r\n\r\nHere is the first implementation. I think it can be improved by adding the mapping of `startDelivery , endDelivery, startDeliveredPercent` values for special accounts.\r\n```\r\ncontract DelayedDeliveryToken is MintableToken {\r\n    \r\n    uint public startDelivery;\r\n    uint public endDelivery;\r\n    uint oublic startDeliveredPercent;\r\n    mapping (address => uint256) public initialBalance;\r\n\r\n    function DelayedDeliveryToken(uint _startDelivery, uint _endDelivery, uint _startDeliveredPercent) public {\r\n        require(_startDelivery < _endDelivery);\r\n        require(_startDeliveredPercent < 100);\r\n        startDelivery = _startDelivery;\r\n        endDelivery = _endDelivery;\r\n        startDeliveredPercent = _startDeliveredPercent;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function mint(address _to, uint256 _amount) public returns (bool) {\r\n        initialBalance[_to] += _amount;\r\n        return super.mint(_to, _amount);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function deliveredBalance(address _account) public constant return (uint256) {\r\n        if (now < startDelivery) {\r\n            return 0;\r\n        }\r\n        if (now >= endDelivery) {\r\n            return initialBalance[_account];\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        uint percent = startDeliveredPercent.add((now - startDelivery).mul(100 - startDeliveredPercent).div(endDelivery - startDelivery));\r\n        return initialBalance[_account].mul(percent).div(100);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function notYetDeliveredBalance(address _account) public constant return (uint256) {\r\n        return initialBalance[_account].sub(deliveredBalance(_account));\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function transfer(address _to, uint256 _value) public returns (bool) {\r\n        require(balanceOf(msg.sender) - _value >= notYetDeliveredBalance(msg.sender));\r\n        return super.transfer(_to, _value);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function transferFrom(address _from, address _to, uint256 _value) public returns (bool) {\r\n        require(balanceOf(_from) - _value >= notYetDeliveredBalance(_from));\r\n        return super.transferFrom(_from, _to, _value);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```",
